Here’s a tight, paste-ready block for the grey box.

**Downgrade cost (A- → BBB) – curve-fit method**

* Assumed take-out: **€9.0bn** ( **€3bn 3y / €3bn 5y / €3bn 7y** )
* Δ i-spread vs A-curve (bps): **+34.1 / +37.6 / +39.9**
* Annual penalty: **€10.24m + €11.29m + €11.98m = €33.5m p.a.**
* Model uncertainty (R²\_B = **0.623** → **±61%**): **€12.9m–€54.1m p.a.**
* PV of extra coupons @ **7.5%** (lives **3/5/7y**): **\~€136m NPV** *(range **€52–€219m**)*

*Method: i-spread $y = m\ln T + c$. A-: $35.185\ln T - 5.974$; B/BBB: $42.06\ln T + 20.591$.*

> Alt “desk comps” view (for a harder stance): assume flat **+145 bps** A-→BBB across tenors ⇒ **\~€130m p.a.**; **\~€520m NPV** (3/5/7y lives @ 7.5%).



