# Grey box (drop-in)

**T0 — Signing**

* **Lock** FX via **deal-contingent Sell DKK / Buy EUR forward** (no CSA, no MTM; only becomes effective if the deal closes).
* Bridge **committed but undrawn**.
* Fees: **upfront** paid at signing; **ticking** starts **D+60**.

**T0→T1 — Pre-close**

* Nothing settles. Only **ticking** (and any **rating step-ups** if delayed).

**T1 — Close (\~9m)**

* **Draw bridge** (pick one):

  * **A)** Draw **DKK** → **settle DCFX** → **receive EUR** → **pay seller**. *(Best match to “fix price in DKK” storyline; refi later into EUR bonds.)*
  * **B)** Draw **EUR** → pay seller in EUR; **cash-settle DCFX** so overall **EUR cost = locked rate**.
* Accounting cue: DCFX becomes effective **only at close**; economics captured at the **locked rate**.

**T2/T3 — Take-out (≤12m post-close)**

* **€9bn EUR bonds + €3bn equity** → **repay bridge** in full (12+6+6 life = **3 windows**).
* Optional: **XCCY swap** if any residual currency mismatch.

**If deal fails**

* **Forward lapses at zero cost**; bridge **never drawn** (only upfront/ticking fees spent).

