## Pricing grid — comps curve method (NIC = +10 bps)

Formulas used: **A-curve** $y=35.185\ln x-5.9744$; **BBB-curve** $y=42.061\ln x+20.951$.
$y=$ i-spread (bps), $x=$ tenor (years). Round to the nearest **1 bps**; show **“\~”** on slide or round to **5 bps** for desk look.

| Tranche    | A-curve i-spr (bps) | +NIC | **Indicative A- (bps)** | **Indicative BBB (bps)** | **BBB uplift** | Rationale                        |
| ---------- | ------------------: | ---: | ----------------------: | -----------------------: | -------------: | -------------------------------- |
| **3-year** |                32.7 |  +10 |              **\~42.7** |               **\~77.2** |      **+34.5** | Bank treasuries / short duration |
| **5-year** |                50.7 |  +10 |              **\~60.7** |               **\~98.6** |      **+38.0** | Core real-money benchmark        |
| **7-year** |                62.5 |  +10 |              **\~72.5** |              **\~112.8** |      **+40.3** | Insurers & pensions              |

Footnote (9pt grey): *Peers fitted to curves; NIC illustrative; update dd/mm/yy. Desk-comps penalty may be larger; curve-based deltas shown here.*

